115 Cases of Fire Reported in Myanmar in January
YANGON , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- A total of 115 fires occurred across Myanmar in January , killing 17 people and wounding 18 others , the official newspaper The official New Light of Myanmar reported Friday .
Myanmar 's fire services departments are taking preventive measures throughout the country for reduction of fires especially in the forthcoming summer season which lasts from the end of February to the beginning of June .
The fires also destroyed 178 houses , three factories and five warehouses , leaving 817 people homeless and 200 animals dead , the report said .
Of the fires , 98 were due to negligence , 10 to electric shock and four to arson , it said .
